Description: Believe I Am enables runners to achieve their goals in both sport and life.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: The idea for Believe I Am was sparked on a run, when two professional runners and #sistersinsport Roisin McGettigan-Dumas + Lauren Fleshman, yearned to share their hard fought lessons and useful tools they amassed over the years, and find a way to share them with the wider running community.  Ro had the idea to create a training journal! It was the one thing, besides her running shoes, that she couldn’t live without as an athlete. She had began the practice of logging her training as a teenager, and it coincided with the time she took ownership of her running and her performances. The practice of journaling stayed with her as she moved to the USA for college, competed in the NCAA system, internationally as a pro, and finally in the Olympics and World Championships. She also tracked her training through her pregnancies and still does in her retirement from professional racing. All of the apps, GPS watches, fitness trackers etc, just couldn’t replace the ritual of banking her training by writing it down with pen and paper. Her journals have become her own personal history.

Full Description: Established in Illinois in 2000, Validation & Technical Services Integrated Inc. (VTSI) has headquarters located in the Des Plaines, USA.  VTSI is an amalgamation of technical and compliance professionals from the Pharmaceutical industry.  The company is a one-source, full-service firm providing Regulatory Compliance, Engineering, Equipment Design and Supply, Commissioning, Validation, Quality System, and Manufacturing Services on a turnkey- and consulting-basis. VTSI serves a wide spectrum of businesses in the United States, Europe, Middle East, and Asia.  These businesses range from FDA-regulated industries (such as International Pharmaceutical, Biological, In-vitro Diagnostic, Medical Devices, and Active Pharmaceutical Ingredients) to non-regulated chemical industries.  Based on the client’s needs, VTSI provides turnkey services or secondary services in new facility design, facility or process upgrades, start-up, and validation.  VTSI works in coordination with the client’s overall project plan. As the worldwide healthcare industry continues its transformation and the regulatory agencies (FDA, MCA, EU, TGA, and local health departments and ministries) change their interpretation of current Good Manufacturing Practices (cGMP) as situations evolve, VTSI consultants listen carefully to each client’s objectives, needs, and challenges before offering insight and guidance.  VTSI designs solutions to best fit client requirements and budgets.
